File: NPA JOHANNESBURG - The National Prosecuting Authority is going to court to ensure Gupta assets remain in state custody. The High Court in Bloemfontein will hear arguments on Thursday in confirmation of the restraint order granted in favour of the NPA. READ: NPA seeks Interpol assistance for Guptas arrest This relates to assets belonging to Atul and Rajesh Gupta and their associate Iqbal Sharma. The interim restraint order was granted in June 2021. Some of the assets include Sharma's R12-million Sandton home and Gupta houses in Constantia and Saxonwold, worth R21-million R12-million respectively.